<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Biology and Genetics (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6248</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">CSE 101</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Introduction to Programming</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2+2+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">24.06.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">This course will provide a hands-on introduction to programming using Python to students with little or no prior experience in programming computers. The course will focus on planning and organizing programs, as well as the grammar of the Python programming language. Lectures will be interactive featuring in-class exercises with lots of support from the course staff. More advanced concepts in computer programming and software development will be introduced in the later stages of the course.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=412837&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Biology and Genetics (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6248</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">MBG 211</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Biostatistics</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">1+2+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2,5</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">18.09.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Basic statistical concepts, data presentation and summarization, probability and probability distributions, parameter estimation and confidence interval calculations, hypothesis testing, linear regression, and the application of all techniques using the R programming language.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=412992&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Biology and Genetics (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6248</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">MBG 221</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Cellular Biology I</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+4+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">5</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">13.02.2026</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">This course examines the molecular architecture and functioning of the cell, the fundamental unit of life, from the perspective of cell chemistry, bioenergetics, and the structural dynamics of proteins. The curriculum deeply examines biophysical processes such as the structure of cell membranes, the transport of small molecules, and their electrical properties, as well as the organization of intracellular compartments and protein sorting mechanisms. Theoretical instruction is supported by comprehensive practical training ranging from basic techniques such as micropipette use, solution preparation, and pH meter in the laboratory environment to advanced molecular methods such as DNA/RNA isolation, centrifugation, and spectrophotometric analyses, enabling the microscopic analysis and visualization of cells.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=412908&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Biology and Genetics (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6248</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">MBG 223</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Genetics</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+4+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">5</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">24.06.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Throughout the course concepts like DNA, chromosomes and their organization, mutations and their repair mechanisms, mitosis, meiosis, pedigrees, Mendelian Genetics and extensions, population genetics will
be discussed. Moreover the students will gain hands on experience about transmission genetics by using Drosophila as a model organism</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=413012&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Biology and Genetics (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6248</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">PHY 101</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Physics I</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+2+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">24.06.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">In this course, we will examine the basic principles of physics to understand the working mechanisms of biological systems, such as vectors, motion in one dimension, motion in two dimensions, Newton&apos;s laws, work and energy, momentum, fluid mechanics, heat and thermodynamics.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=413010&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Biology and Genetics (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6248</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">CSE 102</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Programming Practice</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">2+2+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">24.06.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">From filtering spam to recommending movies, books and music to end-users, the course content is mainly based on practical applications. All students are required to complete a set of mini projects which will allow students to practice what they learn in the classroom by building practical applications.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=413025&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Biology and Genetics (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6248</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">MBG 216</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Bioinformatics</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">24.06.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">During the course, access to data banks, DNA and protein sequences comparison, genomics, transcriptomix and structural bioinformatics will be covered.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=412850&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Biology and Genetics (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6248</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">MBG 222</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Cellular Biology II</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">24.06.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Intracellular membrane traficking; Energy conversion :mitochondria and chloroplasts; Cellular signalling; Cytoskeleton;Cell cycle;Cell death</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=413024&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Biology and Genetics (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6248</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">MBG 224</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Genetics</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+4+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">5</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">16.07.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Mutation and variation; Recombinant DNA technologies; Human genome project; Molecular, biochemical and cellular basis of genetic disease; Cancer genetics; Treatment of genetic diseases; Genomic and personalised medicine; Laboratory techniques used in molecular genetics</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=413023&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Biology and Genetics (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6248</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">PHY 102</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Physics II</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+2+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">24.06.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">In this course, Basic Subject, Concept and Principles of Electricity and Magnetism is going to be learned. (We will examine topics such as Coulomb&apos;s Law, Electric Fields, Electric Flux, Gauss&apos;s Law, Electric Potential, Capacitance and Dielectric, Current and Resistance, Direct Current Circuits, Magnetic Fields.)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=413019&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Biology and Genetics (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6248</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BME 419</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=448551&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Biology and Genetics (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6248</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BME 506</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Medical Image Processing</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">7</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">24.06.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The course will introduce the basic physical principles that enable information about the tissues in the body to be received in the form of signals, taking into account the main physical principles used, under 4 main headings: transmission-based methods (for example, X-ray), reflection-based methods (for example, Ultrasound), emission-based methods (in ex. SPECT / PET) and resonance-based methods (MRI / fMRI).</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=412872&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Biology and Genetics (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6248</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BME 510</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Biosensors</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">7</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">24.06.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Overview of biosensor applications,Desired characteristics of biosensors,Chemical reactions,Enzymes,Cells,Antibodies,Nucleic Acids (RNA and DNA),Labels,Immobilization, Seismic (mass) and thermal sensors, Electrochemical sensors, Optical sensors</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=412873&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Biology and Genetics (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6248</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BME 524</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Nanomedicine</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">7</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">24.06.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Principles of NanoBioTechnology and its main applications in medicine areas, Properties of a nanomedicine platform and its design strategies, Outstanding studies in recent literature.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=412874&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Biology and Genetics (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6248</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BME 530</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Polymeric Biomaterials</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">7</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">24.06.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The multidisciplinary subject of biomedical application of materials obtained from natural and synthetic sources. Solid properties, various materials used in biomaterials, tissue-material interactions, in situ, in vitro and in vivo application methods and sterilization are discussed. Important soft and hard tissue applications involving tissue engineering, drug delivery, implant design, and imaging are discussed with special emphasis on bio and synthetic polymers.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=412875&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Biology and Genetics (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6248</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BME 531</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Selected Topics in Biological Mass Spectrometry</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">7</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">24.06.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">intact-reduced mass, peptide mapping, post-translation modification, glycan analysis, disulfide bond analysis of monoclonal antibodies via mass spectrometric techniques</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=412876&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Biology and Genetics (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6248</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BME 537</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Biomems</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">7</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">24.06.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">This course introduces students to the multi-disciplinary and exciting field of MicroElectroMechanical Systems (MEMS). It teaches the underlying physical principles, methods of fabrication (hard and soft lithography techniques, 3D printing, thin-film deposition, and materials printing) and applications of a broad range of mechanical and optical devices and systems as well as biomedical systems (BioMEMS).</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=412877&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Biology and Genetics (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6248</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BME 541</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Culture of Cells in Tissue Engineering</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">7</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">24.06.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Basic principles of cell culture are given and the main focus is on procedures for obtaining, manipulating, and using cell sources for tissue engineering. Limited number of diverse, important, and successful tissue engineering systems are discussed by providing both the general background and the detailed protocols for each tissue engineering system.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=412878&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Biology and Genetics (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6248</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BME 542</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Advances in Biomaterials</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">7</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">24.06.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Latest developments in the Biomaterials field will be introduced with special emphasis on biocompatibility of materials, sterilization of biomedical devices, tissue engineering and cell biomaterials interactions, drug delivery via biodegradable vehicles, hard tissue implants and bone cements.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=412879&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Biology and Genetics (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6248</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BME 543</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Advanced Cell Culture Techniques in Tissue Engineering</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">7</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">24.06.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Basic principles of cell culture are given and the main focus is on procedures for obtaining, manipulating, and using cell sources for tissue engineering. Limited number of diverse, important, and successful tissue engineering systems are discussed by providing both the general background and the detailed protocols for each tissue engineering system.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=412856&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Biology and Genetics (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6248</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BME 544</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Photosensitisers for Photodynamic Applications</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">7</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">24.06.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Introduction of photodynamic therapy (PDT) principles and mechanisms, introduction to the chemistry of porphyrinoids are explained.
Porphyrin-based and Phthalocyanine-based photosensitizers for anti-cancer PDT,targeting strategies for anti-cancer PDT,Nanoparticles &amp; theranostics in anti-cancer PDT,other types of photosensitizers and antimicrobial PDT are explained.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=412857&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Biology and Genetics (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6248</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BME 545</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Tissue Engineering and Scaffold Desing</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">7</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">24.06.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Principles of tissue engineering and its main application areas, Properties of a suitable scaffold and its design strategies, Outstanding studies in recent literature</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=412858&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Biology and Genetics (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6248</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BME 546</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Theranostic Nanoparticles</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">7</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">24.06.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Introduction of theranostic nanoparticle types and some imaging methods.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=412859&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Biology and Genetics (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6248</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BME 554</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Advances in Ophthalmic Biotechnology</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">7</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">24.06.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Microfabrication, Micropatterning of Substrates and cells, Microfluidics, Molecular Biology on a chip, BioMEMS for Cell Biology Tissue Microengineering, Implantable Microdevices</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=412860&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Biology and Genetics (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6248</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BMT 501</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Fundamentals of Biyomaterials</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">9</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">24.06.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The content of this course consists of the basic structures, types and application fields of biomaterials, changes in the properties of the biomaterials according to their types (metal, ceramic, polymer, composite), the tissue response to these materials, the use of biomaterials in soft and hard tissues, the nano-sized biomaterials, and, the standards and regulations for use of biomaterials.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=412880&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Biology and Genetics (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6248</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">BMT 505</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Principles of Cell and Tissue Culture</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">9</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">24.06.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Includes equipment, media and materials necessary for the mammalian cell culture, identification of different cell types, characterization of cells and cell differentiation, growth kinetics and continuity of culture, Quantitation, cytotoxicity tests, contamination problems, specialized cells and stem cells</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=412881&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Biology and Genetics (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6248</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">MBG 012</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Epigenetics</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">7</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">24.06.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Epigenetic concepts and the questions it tries to define, DNA packaging, histones and histone modifications, Epigenetic mechanisms, Inheritance of epigenetic mechanisms, Epigenetic silencing and ncRNA in epigenetic silencing, Relationship between histone modifications and DNA methylation, Relationship between human diseases and epigenetic changes, Epigenetics phenomena and interactions, epigenetic reprogramming and development, pluripotency and preservation and differentiation of embryonic stem cells, the concept of epigenetic therapy, Epigenetic studies, methods and databases used in epigenetic studies, Epigenetic analysis methods.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=413009&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Biology and Genetics (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6248</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">MBG 013</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Developmental Biology</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">7</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">24.06.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Developmental biology: the formation of three main lineages starting from fertilization, followed by the formation of organs developing from these developmental layers, is explained from the perspective of molecular biology within the framework of embryogenesis.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=413011&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Biology and Genetics (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6248</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">MBG 014</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Proteoimics</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">7</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">27.01.2026</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Proteomics, which enables the analysis of all proteins or their modified forms found in cells, tissues, organs, biological fluids, or organisms, will be discussed. Protein structures, protein and peptide separation techniques, the components of mass spectrometry and various mass analyzers, analyzing and interpreting mass spectrometry results, quantitative proteomics approaches, and protein-protein interactions constitute the course topics. In addition, the applications of different proteomic methods in various medical and biological fields will be examined, such as the discovery of disease biomarkers or the comparison of protein post-translational modifications in different cellular states.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=412838&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Biology and Genetics (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6248</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">MBG 015</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">DNA Repair and Mutgenesis</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">7</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">24.06.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">In this course, mutagenic agents, DNA damages and structural damages, DNA damage repair pathways, nucleus and mitochondrial DNA damage repair mechanisms, genetic instabilities, mutations and hereditary diseases caused by DNA damage repair mechanisms malfunctioning subjects will be discussed in detail. Moreover, roles of those systems in diagnosis, etiology and pathology of diseases caused by DNA repair mechanisms and DNA repair errors will be examined.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=412993&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Biology and Genetics (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6248</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">MBG 016</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">RNA World</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">7</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">24.06.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular biology of RNA</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=412839&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Biology and Genetics (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6248</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">MBG 017</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Animal Models of Human Pathology</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">7</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">11.07.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Ethics, Resources and Approaches, The Advent of the Golden Era of Animal Alternatives, Models for disease-oriented topics, including cardiac and pulmonary diseases, aging, infectious diseases, obesity, diabetes, neurological diseases, joint diseases, visual disorders, cancer, hypertension, genetic diseases, and diseases of abuse.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=412836&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Biology and Genetics (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6248</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">MBG 018</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Mechanisms of Disease</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">7</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">24.06.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Key Principles in Disease, Molecular mechanisms of the disease such as Inflammation and Immune Responses, Cardiovascular Diseases, Viral diseases, Aging, Alzheimer’s Disease, Infection and immunity, Cancer overview, Integrative techniques for health and disease, the effect of diet, Model systems for human biology and medicine</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=413014&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Biology and Genetics (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6248</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">MBG 020</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Genetic Counselling</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">7</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">24.06.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Types of genetical diseases, inheritance types, screening and prognosis of genetical diseases, phenotypic properties, genotype and phenotype relationship, evaluation, analysis and explanation of the genetical report, prevention of the genetical diseases</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=413013&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Biology and Genetics (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6248</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">MBG 021</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Research Project Management</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">7</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">18.09.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The course covers the general features of a research project. Topics include conducting a literature review to define gaps or problems, determining the goals and objectives for a solution-focused project proposal, research planning, creating work packages and writing methodologies, understanding the ethical aspects of research, project management and budgeting. Course activities include examining project proposal examples and calls for proposals, deconstructing research articles, designing and writing new project proposals, peer-reviewing them, and presenting them.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=412989&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Biology and Genetics (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6248</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">MBG 022</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Structural Biology</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">7</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">24.06.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Specifics of protein structures</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=412871&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Biology and Genetics (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6248</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">MBG 023</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Plant Biology and Ecology</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">7</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">16.02.2026</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The foundations of evolution, plant diversity and origin, the evolutionary developments of plants, the fundamentals and components of ecology, population ecology, communities, biodiversity, energy and food webs and nutrient cycles, the basics of plant biotechnology.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=412990&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Biology and Genetics (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6248</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">MBG 024</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Biophysics</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">7</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">24.06.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Teaching Method: Lecture in the form of lectures, question-answer, group homework, slide
Introduction to biophysics and atom, molecule, matter; concepts of radioactivity, communication of radiation with matter, biological effects; water and aqueous solutions as living environment; osmosis, dialysis, surface tension; structure and functions of cell membrane; membrane proteins, channel channels; material transport across biological membranes; structure and functions of biomolecules; energy flow in living things, thermodynamic laws, thermodynamic properties of water; ATP and chemical energy transmission; cell breathing; free energy change of electron transfer chain; bioelectric potentials and biophysical bases of muscle contraction; biomechanics; bioenergetic properties of muscle contraction; heart muscle and smooth muscle; It covers communication biophysics and biophysical research methods.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=413018&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Biology and Genetics (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6248</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">MBG 025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Biology of Cancer</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">7</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">21.10.2025</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The Biology and Genetics of Cells and Organisms; The Nature of Cancer; Tumor Viruses; Cellular Oncogenes; Growth Factors and Receptors; Cytoplasmic Signaling Circuitry Programs; Tumor Suppressor Genes; pRb and Control of the Cell Cycle Clock; p53 and Apoptosis; The Hallmarks of Cancer</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=412907&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Molecular Biology and Genetics (English)</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">6248</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">MBG 026</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Stem Cell and Therapy</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">7</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">12.02.2026</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Stem cells and their general properties and signalling pathways, types of stem cells, organoids and clinical applications, stem cells and ethical regulations</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=413022&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
